RESEARCH_MUNICIPALITY.notes: Lynnwood, WA operates under a mayor-council government. Christine Frizzell is the current Mayor, having taken office in January 2022. The City Council consists of seven members elected at-large. The listed council members are based on the official City of Lynnwood website. Recent election results from November 2025 indicate that Derica Escamilla and Robert Leutwyler retained their seats, and Isabel Mata and Bryce Owings were also elected. The county was expected to certify election results on November 25, 2025, which may lead to changes in the council's composition from the currently listed members.
